      "role": "user",
      "content": "self-acceptance feels like a joke when you've lost everything. i'm not talking about a new way to play, i'm talking about the fact that the person i was is dead. the version of me that people actually liked and respected is gone for good. it feels more like there's just an empty space where a person used to be. why should i bother trying to \"embrace\" a shell of a person? it just feels like an endless, exhausting weight.",
